section.section:
The application shall include as to proposed electronic terminals:
The location of each;
The physical size and other characteristics;
The capital investment;
The security devices to be installed;
The systems and safeguards to be used to insure confidentiality and privacy of the account information of customers; and
Evidence of sufficient fidelity, forgery, and other appropriate insurance to protect the interests of the association.

text.section:
A savings and loan association may use an electronic terminal to enable a customer of the association to:
Deposit money into an account of the customer of the association;
Transfer money from any account of the customer to any other account;
Withdraw money from an account or under an authorized line of credit of a customer;
Make payments on loans; and
Execute any other transaction that the Division Director approves.
